Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people check their phone the moment they wake up. Marcus Aurelius asked himself three questions instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Before news\, before messages\, before the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.33,0:00:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,got to him—Marcus Aurelius paused. In silence\,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he asked himself three questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.00,0:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One: 'What am I avoiding that I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should lean into?' He faced discomfort before
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.00,0:00:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,breakfast—because growth lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Two: 'What can I control today?' He
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.33,0:00:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,drew a mental line—inside the circle: action\,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,focus\, breath. Outside? Noise. Judgment. Chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.99,0:00:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Three: 'How will I make others better?'
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.25,0:00:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not 'what can I get'—but 'what can
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.50,0:00:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I give?' That shift? It armored his
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.75,0:00:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,mind.
